1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:09,360
If you want to make it hard,
go ahead and tell your mom.

2
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:14,000
But remember, Pun, the person
who will be hurt the most is your mom.

3
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:16,160
Why can't we talk about it nicely?

4
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:18,440
- Will throwing a tantrum solve anything?
- Throwing a tantrum?

5
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,160
I've never thrown a tantrum, Pun.

6
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,560
I'm just protecting myself.

7
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,320
Don't talk to me like that!

8
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,880
- I won't let you go.
- Pun, don't!

9
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,400
- <i>Come back, Pie!</i>
- <i>Let her go.</i>

10
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,160
I've tried my best.

11
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:37,040
<i>But it's just too much.</i>

12
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:39,960
It's my fault. I'm stressed about Dad,

13
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,560
<i>and I ended up taking it out on her.</i>

14
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:42,520
Take care of Pie for me.

15
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,000
You be nice to Win, okay?

16
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:47,400
<i>Don't argue and mess up the work.</i>

17
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:49,760
We can be friends. Trust me.

18
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,040
Let me put it on.

19
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,560
Turn around.

20
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,600
All done.

21
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,880
Thanks for helping me.

22
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:36,400
No need to thank me. It's part of my job.

23
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,720
Huh?

24
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:41,680
You got hurt getting the file
for the grandma.

25
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:43,240
So it counts as part of my job.

26
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,760
What kind of reasoning is that, Pie?

27
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,560
Wouldn't it be easier to admit
that you took care of my wound?

28
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,920
I'm being serious.

29
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,520
What happened between us was long ago.

30
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:02,920
We both went our separate ways,
until you got married.

31
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,720
So why are you still angry with me?

32
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,560
I already have too much on my mind.

33
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:18,200
I don't want anything else.
Let's not talk about it.

34
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,080
Hello.

35
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,280
Is that you, Pie?

36
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:34,160
Oh, Aunt Saen!

37
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:36,440
Aunt Saen!

38
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:38,240
- Hello.
- Hello.

39
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,520
You're as beautiful as ever.

40
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,800
Thank you so much.

41
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:42,720
I'm so happy you still remember me.

42
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,440
Of course, I remember you, Aunt Saen.
I could never forget.

43
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:48,000
Why did you walk in
looking so stressed just now?

44
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:48,920
Hold on.

45
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,040
Did that brat give you another headache?

46
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,760
Auntie.

47
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:54,480
Did you come up here
just to stir things up?

48
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:57,040
Well. But Pie really did look stressed.

49
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:00,720
- So, did you two have a fight?
- Auntie!

50
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,800
No, not at all.

51
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:06,520
Well, I usually look serious, don't I?

52
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:10,720
I think it makes me look focused at work,
like I'm deep in thought.

53
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:12,800
Nice answer.

54
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,280
So what are you doing here?

55
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:18,760
I told you I'd come see you
as soon as I finished work.

56
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:19,920
What?

57
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,280
Miss your nephew so much
you had to come up?

58
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,360
Hey.

59
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:24,880
I'm not the one who missed you.

60
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:29,640
Someone came looking for you,
said she missed you, so I brought her up.

61
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,320
Who?

62
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:34,800
The one you met while studying in Japan.

63
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,480
No way!

64
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,600
Run!

65
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:54,600
- Win!
- Hey!

66
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,400
You punk!

67
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,120
You're hitting me the moment you arrive?

68
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,920
You came back and disappeared.

69
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,040
I couldn't reach you. I'm still mad.

70
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:08,360
- Sorry, I've been busy with work.
- Yeah.

71
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,640
Run, this is Pie.

72
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:13,880
She's my coworker.

73
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:19,280
This is Run, the owner of the restaurant
I worked at in Japan.

74
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,800
- Hello, Run.
- Hello.

75
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:24,240
Saen told me Win's working with you here.

76
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,160
Yes.

77
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:28,880
Well, Khao Soi is really popular
in Japan right now.

78
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:31,800
I wanted to find authentic seasoning.

79
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:33,400
That's why I came to Thailand.

80
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,760
- Right.
- I see.

81
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:37,760
She went looking for you at the homestay,
but couldn't find you.

82
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:39,640
That's why I had to bring her up here.

83
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:43,240
See? I didn't even get lost.
Pretty impressive, right?

84
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,280
Want your nephew to praise you now?

85
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,160
Yes.

86
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,760
- Very impressive.
- Come here. I missed you.

87
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:49,800
- Give me a hug.
- Come here.

88
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,240
- Missed you too.
- Missed you.

89
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:55,440
Hey, am I interrupting your work?

90
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:58,560
Oh, not at all.
It's break time right now anyway.

91
00:07:58,640 --> 00:07:59,800
Well, I'll let you two catch up.

92
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,120
I should get back to work.

93
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,240
Alright, thanks.

94
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,440
Yes. Goodbye, Run.

95
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,840
- See you later, Aunt Saen.
- Sure.

96
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:05,400
Kaew, what are you doing?

97
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,920
I'm about to take these fruits over.
I just picked them.

98
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:08,920
I see.

99
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,320
Then let me help.

100
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,040
Sure.

101
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:15,120
- Do these need washing?
- Yes.

102
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,240
Got it.

103
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,320
Alright.

104
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,560
Kaew, you can go rest first if you want.

105
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:23,960
I'll take care of this,
and I'll bring them over myself.

106
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:26,120
- Alright, thank you so much.
- Yes.

107
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,720
- I'm so stiff from the ride.
- Here.

108
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:38,880
Thanks.

109
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,240
Hey.

110
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,280
How was Win doing at work over there?

111
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,640
Did he ever slack off?

112
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:46,920
Come on. Don't say that about him.

113
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,960
He's been a huge help,
always working hard.

114
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:52,320
Win? Really?

115
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,160
I can hardly believe it.

116
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,000
Seriously.

117
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:00,800
He's probably the hardest worker
in the whole restaurant.

118
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,800
He never took a single day off.

119
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:07,560
And girls were always
asking him out, remember?

120
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,760
But he said he wasn't interested
in anyone there.

121
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:13,040
He was saving up to come back
and propose to a girl in Thailand.

122
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,760
No idea who she was, though.

123
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,240
But he was dead serious.

124
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:31,480
Every time I asked,
he'd say he wanted more money,

125
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:35,280
wanted to be a better man,
so her mom wouldn't look down on him.

126
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:38,600
He wanted to be rich enough
to take care of her daughter.

127
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:40,920
Run, keep it down.

128
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,320
People will hear. It's embarrassing.

129
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,720
What's embarrassing?

130
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:47,080
Good things like this
should be shared, Saen.

131
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:49,320
So, how'd it go?

132
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,800
Did you propose to her yet?

133
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,560
If there's good news,

134
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:59,560
don't forget to invite me.

135
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:02,680
I'll fly back to Thailand, close the shop,
and come celebrate with Saen.

136
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:07,920
That's not happening anymore.

137
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,160
She's married now.

138
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,520
What?

139
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:13,800
Seriously?

140
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:19,640
Win, after all that studying,

141
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:23,920
working so hard and saving all that money,
turning down every girl there,

142
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:26,480
just to come back and get dumped?

143
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,360
Win.

144
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:38,120
I just noticed we have two guests.
I brought extra glasses.

145
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:46,280
Can you manage that? Here, let me help.

146
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,760
Please have some fruit.

147
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,320
It's freshly picked.

148
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:57,080
Go ahead and eat. Don't wait for me.

149
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,000
Hey, Win! Where are you going?

150
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,440
Pie!

151
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:13,680
The woman in Thailand
Run was talking about, who is she?

152
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,840
There's only been one woman in my life

153
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:23,880
who made me want to change myself.

154
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,840
- That woman is--
- Stop.

155
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,280
I don't want to know anymore.

156
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,440
Whoever it is, it doesn't matter.

157
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:34,280
It is you, Pie!

158
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:01,160
I'm not ashamed to say it.

159
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:04,280
Back then, I really was working hard
and saving money.

160
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,600
Because I had nothing, no job,

161
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:09,880
no money, no parents.

162
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,720
Nothing worthy of you.

163
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:19,560
I had to build everything from scratch
before I had the courage to come back.

164
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:22,960
And I was devastated

165
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,520
when I found out you married Pun.

166
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:39,880
I'm not saying all this

167
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,880
because I want anything.

168
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:47,320
If Run hadn't come and brought this up,

169
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,640
I never would've told you.

170
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,400
Why?

171
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,360
Because there's no point.

172
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:21,360
We've come too far.

173
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:32,680
Yes.

174
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,480
We really have.

175
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,480
I just want you to know…

176
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:50,760
I'm still the same.

177
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:57,000
The feelings I have for you
haven't changed.

178
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:02,680
But no matter what
my place is in your life,

179
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:06,960
I'll always stay by your side.

180
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,360
No matter how much you change,

181
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,840
I'm still the same person.

182
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:52,040
Pie.

183
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,320
Can we be friends?

184
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:19,400
Thank you, Pie.

185
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:28,640
I should get back to work.

186
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:51,440
<i>He's probably the hardest worker</i>
<i>in the whole restaurant.</i>

187
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:54,320
<i>He never took a single day off.</i>

188
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,640
<i>And girls were always</i>
<i>asking him out, remember?</i>

189
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:59,920
<i>But he said he wasn't interested</i>
<i>in anyone there.</i>

190
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,240
<i>He was saving up to come back</i>
<i>and propose to a girl in Thailand.</i>

191
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:04,400
<i>No idea who she was, though.</i>

192
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,640
<i>But he was dead serious.</i>

193
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,120
<i>Every time I asked,</i>

194
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:14,000
<i>he'd say he wanted more money,</i>
<i>wanted to be a better man,</i>

195
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:15,960
<i>so her mom wouldn't look down on him.</i>

196
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:18,760
<i>He wanted to be rich enough</i>
<i>to take care of her daughter.</i>

197
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,760
Come on in.

198
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:22,760
If you need anything else,
just let me know.

199
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:24,720
Thank you so much.

200
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,680
Alright then, I'll leave you to it.

201
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:28,480
Sure. Thank you.

202
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:38,120
<i>Mink, I need some advice.</i>

203
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:39,880
<i>How do I make it up to Pie?</i>

204
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:43,560
<i>However you do it,</i>
<i>let it come from the heart.</i>

205
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:46,440
<i>If you were wrong,</i>
<i>apologize and be honest with her.</i>

206
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:49,160
<i>But there is a little cheat code</i>
<i>for making up.</i>

207
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:51,520
<i>A cheat code?</i>

208
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:53,280
<i>What is it?</i>

209
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:54,680
<i>A surprise.</i>

210
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:58,280
<i>A surprise can melt away her anger.</i>

211
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:01,240
<i>Try doing something</i>
<i>you've never done before,</i>

212
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,600
<i>something Pie would never expect from you.</i>

213
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:05,920
<i>Give it a try.</i>

214
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:50,320
Pie.

215
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:52,360
Can I talk to you for a moment?

216
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,400
Sure.

217
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:55,600
Well.

218
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:59,080
About yesterday, I'm sorry

219
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:02,080
for bringing up how Win saved up
to propose to someone.

220
00:23:02,160 --> 00:23:05,760
I didn't know you were the one
he had his heart set on.

221
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:11,240
But everything I said was the truth, Pie.

222
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:13,960
I wasn't saying it
just to make him look good.

223
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:16,040
I meant every word.

224
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:19,200
I'm leaving today.

225
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:21,080
So I wanted to clear things up for him.

226
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:24,840
If there's been any misunderstanding
between you two, I want to clear it up.

227
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:30,200
Win really is a good person, Pie.

228
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:32,600
He's determined, sincere, and serious.

229
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,520
I know him well.

230
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:37,160
I'm not exaggerating
just to make him look good.

231
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:43,880
Pie, I truly believe

232
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:47,880
everything that happens in this world
has a meaning.

233
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,680
The fact that I happened to come here,

234
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:53,840
I think it must mean something.

235
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:56,720
And if it's something good,

236
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:58,840
that would make me happy.

237
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:09,120
Thank you so much, Run.

238
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,960
Alright then, I should get going.

239
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,120
Goodbye.

240
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,480
Good luck, Pie.

241
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:22,200
Thank you so much.

242
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:23,880
Not at all.

243
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:51,720
- Come on.
- There you go.

244
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:54,160
- One each. Don't fight over them.
- Here, one each.

245
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:55,560
Take it easy.

246
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:57,520
- There's enough for everyone.
- Yeah. Wait.

247
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:59,160
- One each, okay?
- Alright.

248
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:02,120
Here. The little ones
haven't gotten theirs yet.

249
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,480
- Got one? Okay.
- Yeah.

250
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:04,880
- Share with the younger kids.
- This way!

251
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:06,800
- Share with the younger kids too.
- Me too!

252
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:08,520
- Be good, okay?
- Yay!

253
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:11,520
They really love it.

254
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,360
- Such little troublemakers.
- So cute.

255
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:15,880
I'm heading off now.

256
00:25:18,120 --> 00:25:19,000
Give me a hug.

257
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:21,920
- I'll miss you. Take care of yourself.
- Okay.

258
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:25,560
- Give me a kiss.
- Hey!

259
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:28,680
What, are you shy now?

260
00:25:28,760 --> 00:25:31,080
Can't even touch you a little?

261
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:33,800
Keep your spirits up.

262
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:36,400
I'm off now.

263
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:38,520
- See you again.
- Bye, Run.

264
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:39,960
Alright.

265
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:41,720
Bye!

266
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:43,680
Bye!

267
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:45,000
Bye!

268
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:47,000
- See you, Run.
- Yeah.

269
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:49,280
- Take care of yourself.
- Take care of yourself too.

270
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:50,360
Got it!

271
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:55,040
Bye!

272
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:57,960
Bye!

273
00:25:58,040 --> 00:26:02,040
Bye!

274
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:04,520
Bye!

275
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:12,520
Have some water.

276
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:13,880
Thank you.

277
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,880
- Pie.
- Huh?

278
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:52,440
Did you get it all down?

279
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:54,240
Of course.

280
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:10,640
A lot of detail
went into getting this result.

281
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,320
- Yes.
- Grandma?

282
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:13,840
Here.

283
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:15,560
Grandma!

284
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,680
Hold on, Grandma!

285
00:27:17,760 --> 00:27:19,240
Hey, don't!

286
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:21,520
Stop!

287
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:23,200
Hey!

288
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:24,360
Don't do that!

289
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,080
Wait!

290
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:28,720
You too?

291
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:11,640
While we're waiting for the ride,
want to go for a walk?

292
00:28:13,520 --> 00:28:15,280
Sure, let's go.

293
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:49,880
- Pie.
- Yes?

294
00:28:52,720 --> 00:28:54,080
We've cleared everything up, right?

295
00:28:57,480 --> 00:28:59,600
Whatever we started together here,

296
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,840
let's end it well here today.

297
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:06,120
Sure.

298
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:09,520
From now on,
let's be good friends to each other.

299
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,160
Thank you so much.

300
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,440
And…

301
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:18,080
I'll start by being a good friend
to you first.

302
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:21,080
How?

303
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:22,720
By…

304
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:24,840
taking this medicine.

305
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:29,600
So you won't have to watch me throw up.

306
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:32,840
Fine, I won't put up with it then.
Take the whole pack.

307
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:34,960
Isn't that a bit much?

308
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:37,040
Finish it all. We're out of vomit bags.

309
00:29:37,120 --> 00:29:38,360
No shops on the mountain.

310
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:41,360
Come on. Take them all.
How many are there?

311
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,840
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight. Ten pills.

312
00:29:44,560 --> 00:29:46,720
If I take all of that, I'll die.

313
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:27,080
<i>The fact that I happened to come here,</i>

314
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:31,240
<i>I think it must mean something.</i>

315
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:34,040
<i>And if it's something good,</i>

316
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:36,120
<i>that would make me happy.</i>

317
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:16,920
I hope your mom gets better soon.

318
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,440
Thanks so much.

319
00:31:18,520 --> 00:31:20,120
Mom just took her meds and fell asleep.

320
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:22,000
I'll tell her you stopped by.

321
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:24,480
Too bad you missed Dad.

322
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:26,400
He went to grab some food.

323
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:28,640
Hey, sit down first.
I'll get you some water.

324
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:31,480
If you hadn't posted on Instagram
that your mom was sick,

325
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:33,840
I wouldn't have known you were home.

326
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:35,360
I thought you'd gone to Mae Hong Son.

327
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:36,600
Yeah.

328
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:37,960
It was sudden.

329
00:31:38,040 --> 00:31:40,600
I was just about to fly out
when Mom collapsed.

330
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:42,920
So I had to cancel.

331
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:44,480
Here, water.

332
00:31:44,560 --> 00:31:45,960
So did Pie go alone?

333
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:48,160
No, she went with Win.

334
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:49,880
They're probably fighting by now.

335
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:53,320
Worry about your mom first.

336
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:57,160
Pie's tough enough to move all her stuff
out of Pun's house already.

337
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,280
Why worry about her?

338
00:31:58,360 --> 00:31:59,280
What?!

339
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:00,880
You didn't know?

340
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:01,960
And how do you know?

341
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:02,880
Pun told me.

342
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:05,040
Then why didn't he tell me?

343
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:07,480
I'm his secretary and Pie's best friend.

344
00:32:07,560 --> 00:32:08,760
He should've told me.

345
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:11,240
Why'd he tell you?

346
00:32:11,840 --> 00:32:12,960
That's weird.

347
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:14,800
So what's going on with you two?

348
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:15,760
Are you close now?

349
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:17,320
Playing the role of his advisor?

350
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:20,640
Whatever role Pun gives me, I'll take it.

351
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:24,360
Easy there.

352
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:27,480
Even if Pie moved out,
they haven't broken up yet.

353
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:29,760
Couples fight all the time.

354
00:32:30,320 --> 00:32:32,120
If you start getting cozy
with Pun right now,

355
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:34,560
people are gonna see you
as the other woman.

356
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:37,360
Let them think what they want.
I don't care.

357
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:40,240
You know it goes both ways.

358
00:34:09,239 --> 00:34:12,280
DIVORCE

359
00:34:30,199 --> 00:34:32,400
DIVORCE

360
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:35,000
HOW DO YOU FILE FOR DIVORCE?

361
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:40,400
MUTUAL CONSENT DIVORCE

362
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:47,600
DIVORCE REGISTRATION

363
00:34:50,440 --> 00:34:53,840
DIVORCE

364
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:57,320
So you want a divorce?

365
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:27,600
MOM

366
00:35:29,280 --> 00:35:30,360
Yes, Mom?

367
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:31,760
<i>Pie.</i>

368
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:34,280
Are you almost here? Where are you now?

369
00:35:35,160 --> 00:35:37,040
I left the airport a little while ago.

370
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:38,160
Is something up, Mom?

371
00:35:38,680 --> 00:35:40,320
No, nothing.

372
00:35:40,400 --> 00:35:44,320
I was just asking, so I can set
the table and wait for you.

373
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,480
<i>Pie, come straight home, okay?</i>

374
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:48,880
Don't stop anywhere.

375
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,160
Okay.

376
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:11,080
<i>How's it going?</i>

377
00:36:11,160 --> 00:36:12,600
<i>How many rounds have you and Pie fought?</i>

378
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:15,520
<i>Take care of yourself. I'm worried.</i>

379
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,360
HOW'S IT GOING?

380
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:29,200
HOW MANY ROUNDS HAVE YOU AND PIE FOUGHT?

381
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:31,640
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF. I'M WORRIED.

382
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:35,200
He replied!

383
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:38,800
He replied!

384
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:55,200
Pun, Pie's almost here.

385
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:57,880
Huh?

386
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,160
Why are you still like this?

387
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:03,720
Is something wrong, Pun?

388
00:37:08,440 --> 00:37:10,680
I'll pay Puk to finish the rest.
I'm heading home.

389
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:12,320
Wait.

390
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:15,160
Pie's almost here. Don't you want
to wait and see her first?

391
00:37:15,240 --> 00:37:16,320
It's okay.

392
00:37:17,120 --> 00:37:18,760
She just got back.

393
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:20,720
Let her rest first, then we'll talk.

394
00:37:22,160 --> 00:37:24,000
There's a lot we need to talk about.

395
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:27,080
I want to talk when I've got a clear head.

396
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:29,280
I'll leave this to you, Puk.

397
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:30,600
Uh, Pun…

398
00:37:31,680 --> 00:37:34,240
Puk, finish this up. I'll be right back.

399
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:36,040
Pun!

400
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:38,360
I guarantee it'll turn out amazing.

401
00:37:41,640 --> 00:37:44,600
Pun! What happened?

402
00:37:45,520 --> 00:37:48,240
Is something bothering you?
You can tell me.

403
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:49,640
Mom.

404
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:52,120
Let me ask you something directly.

405
00:37:52,640 --> 00:37:54,520
Ever since Pie married me,

406
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:57,200
has she ever said she wasn't happy?

407
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:01,840
No, she's been happy with everything.

408
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:03,200
Oh, well.

409
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:06,480
Except maybe your mother.

410
00:38:08,080 --> 00:38:10,160
You should just talk to her,

411
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:14,800
ask her to be more understanding of Pie
and a little kinder.

412
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:17,920
Oh, and she did mention something

413
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:21,520
about walls and keeping a distance,
something like that.

414
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:25,240
I think she sensed you were hiding
the truth about your father.

415
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,920
Pie loves you very much.

416
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:34,440
I see.

417
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:39,600
Mom.

418
00:38:41,120 --> 00:38:43,000
When I was dating Pie,

419
00:38:44,040 --> 00:38:46,960
you told me she'd never had
a boyfriend before,

420
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:49,640
right?

421
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:54,160
That's right.

422
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:56,320
She's never had a boyfriend before.

423
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:59,520
Lots of people pursued her,
but I never let her date anyone.

424
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:03,120
Is something wrong, Pun?

425
00:39:03,200 --> 00:39:05,280
Why are you suddenly asking this?

426
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:06,840
You can tell me.

427
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:09,040
No, nothing.

428
00:39:10,200 --> 00:39:13,000
I was just thinking back
to what we talked about,

429
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:15,040
if I remember correctly.

430
00:39:17,640 --> 00:39:18,760
Yes, that's right.

431
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:21,440
I'll get going now.

432
00:40:36,440 --> 00:40:39,480
Surprise!

433
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:44,680
You're surprised, aren't you, Pie?

434
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:48,880
Pun asked me to come up
and decorate your room this morning.

435
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:51,080
Mr. Pun did it all by himself.

436
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:53,360
I offered to help, but he wouldn't let me.

437
00:40:53,960 --> 00:40:56,080
He's so romantic.

438
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:57,240
Pie.

439
00:40:57,320 --> 00:41:01,240
I told Pun to stay and wait for you,
but he wouldn't.

440
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:03,600
He said you must be tired from the trip,

441
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:06,040
so he'd wait
until you were rested before talking.

442
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:09,040
He probably didn't want to pressure you.

443
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:12,800
Oh my, Pun is such a good man.

444
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:14,640
Pie.

445
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:16,960
Stop being mad at him, okay?

446
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:19,280
Go home and make up with him.

447
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:26,200
Pie.

448
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:28,840
He's done all this for you.

449
00:41:28,920 --> 00:41:30,960
Don't be angry anymore, okay?

450
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:33,240
And call him, dear.

451
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:39,640
At the very least,
call and thank him, okay?

452
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:41,880
Call him now, Pie. Go on, call him.

453
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:45,960
If you won't call, I'll call him myself.

454
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:47,320
- Puk, bring me the phone.
- Yes.

455
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:48,360
Mom.

456
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:50,880
Please don't call. I'll call him myself.

457
00:41:52,360 --> 00:41:54,320
Let me rest first, okay? I'm tired.

458
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:57,240
I'll handle it myself.
You and Puk can go out first.

459
00:41:57,760 --> 00:41:59,080
- Go on, Puk.
- Yes?

460
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:00,280
Let's go downstairs.

461
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:02,000
My daughter needs to talk to her husband.

462
00:42:02,080 --> 00:42:04,600
- Go on.
- Okay.

463
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:11,240
Pie, talk things out nicely, okay?

464
00:42:13,040 --> 00:42:14,040
Okay.

465
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:23,200
HOW ARE YOU? ARE YOU STILL MAD AT ME?

466
00:43:23,280 --> 00:43:25,320
PLEASE PICK UP
CALL ME BACK, OKAY?

467
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:07,680
Rok, where are you right now?

468
00:44:12,360 --> 00:44:15,520
I forgot to tell you
I didn't go to Mae Hong Son.

469
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:19,920
My mom collapsed before I boarded,
so I had to stay and take care of her.

470
00:44:21,640 --> 00:44:23,760
When I talked to Win,
he didn't mention anything.

471
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:27,040
Maybe he forgot. I forgot too.

472
00:44:32,160 --> 00:44:33,480
What's wrong with you today?

473
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:36,520
You look stressed,
and you came to see me this early.

474
00:44:36,600 --> 00:44:37,440
Is something wrong?

475
00:44:38,640 --> 00:44:39,920
I'm having problems with Pie.

476
00:44:41,440 --> 00:44:42,880
I know.

477
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:43,960
What?

478
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:45,520
Did she tell you?

479
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:46,720
No, not at all.

480
00:44:46,800 --> 00:44:49,600
She never told me.
Mink was the one who told me.

481
00:44:50,840 --> 00:44:52,680
Why would you go ask Mink for advice?

482
00:44:52,760 --> 00:44:55,360
If Pie finds out,
what's she going to think?

483
00:44:55,440 --> 00:44:57,560
You took her problem to another woman.

484
00:44:57,640 --> 00:45:01,080
Rok, I came to ask for advice,
not to get scolded.

485
00:45:02,320 --> 00:45:03,640
I'm sorry.

486
00:45:05,880 --> 00:45:07,320
So what do you want advice about?

487
00:45:10,680 --> 00:45:11,920
Before she went up north,

488
00:45:12,880 --> 00:45:14,120
how was Pie?

489
00:45:16,360 --> 00:45:18,600
She seemed stressed, kind of sulky,

490
00:45:18,680 --> 00:45:21,240
since the day you disappeared
and couldn't be reached.

491
00:45:21,320 --> 00:45:22,400
Remember?

492
00:45:33,240 --> 00:45:34,240
No.

493
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:36,640
I don't think it's that.

494
00:45:37,440 --> 00:45:38,280
Hey!

495
00:45:38,360 --> 00:45:39,600
It must be about Aunt Nhun.

496
00:45:39,680 --> 00:45:42,840
Honestly, Pun,
Aunt Nhun is really something.

497
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:44,480
Have you talked to Pie yet?

498
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:47,080
Not yet.

499
00:46:05,560 --> 00:46:07,120
I don't think it's about my mother.

500
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:11,120
And it's not because I was out of reach
for just one day.

501
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:14,040
I think there's something else.

502
00:46:15,680 --> 00:46:16,720
Something else?

503
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:18,480
Rok.

504
00:46:20,400 --> 00:46:22,680
In the past, when Pie
had problems with an ex,

505
00:46:22,760 --> 00:46:23,960
what did she do?

506
00:46:24,720 --> 00:46:27,200
She's never had an ex, Pun.

507
00:46:27,280 --> 00:46:30,760
Her first and only boyfriend is you.

508
00:46:32,320 --> 00:46:33,280
Are you sure?

509
00:46:34,920 --> 00:46:36,120
Absolutely!

510
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:37,760
If there had been someone, I'd know.

511
00:46:37,840 --> 00:46:39,760
I'm way too nosy for that.

512
00:46:41,320 --> 00:46:45,240
If you want to know what she's thinking
or why she moved back to her mom's place,

513
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:47,200
why don't you ask her directly?

514
00:46:47,280 --> 00:46:48,520
That way, you won't have to keep guessing.

515
00:46:50,800 --> 00:46:52,120
I will.

516
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:54,720
But I want more information first.

517
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:56,560
I want to ask when I'm ready.

518
00:46:56,640 --> 00:46:58,080
I hate being lied to.

519
00:46:59,040 --> 00:47:02,440
You're overthinking it, Pun.
Pie's not that kind of person.

520
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:05,680
She's not the type to make things up
or deceive people.

521
00:47:05,760 --> 00:47:08,160
Especially not to someone she loves
or her own family.

522
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:09,440
She'd never do that.

523
00:47:09,520 --> 00:47:11,200
I'd stake my life on it.

524
00:47:24,640 --> 00:47:26,120
You can never be so sure.

525
00:47:28,120 --> 00:47:31,280
Even people who seem trustworthy,
warm, and family-oriented

526
00:47:31,960 --> 00:47:33,600
still lie to their own families.

527
00:47:33,680 --> 00:47:35,360
You see it all the time.

528
00:47:36,360 --> 00:47:37,600
Who's that?

529
00:47:38,560 --> 00:47:39,440
Rok.

530
00:47:41,040 --> 00:47:42,800
Don't tell Pie about this.

531
00:47:42,880 --> 00:47:45,040
Don't say anything.
Don't tell her a thing. Nothing.

532
00:47:45,120 --> 00:47:47,640
Let this stay between Pie and me.

533
00:47:47,720 --> 00:47:48,960
Understand?

534
00:47:50,880 --> 00:47:52,000
Rok.

535
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:54,560
Do you understand what I'm saying?

536
00:47:57,000 --> 00:47:58,880
Okay. I understand.

537
00:48:10,440 --> 00:48:11,840
What is going on?

538
00:48:29,920 --> 00:48:32,560
Koh, are you awake yet?

539
00:48:42,880 --> 00:48:44,080
What's wrong, Pun?

540
00:48:44,760 --> 00:48:46,560
You look like you haven't slept.

541
00:48:48,920 --> 00:48:50,120
I just talked to Rok.

542
00:48:52,760 --> 00:48:54,960
I just found out she wasn't with you
in Mae Hong Son.

543
00:48:57,120 --> 00:48:58,120
Yeah.

544
00:48:59,320 --> 00:49:02,760
I was so caught up with work
that I forgot to tell you.

545
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:09,680
How was it,
just you and Pie in Mae Hong Son?

546
00:49:13,800 --> 00:49:15,280
Pie was focused on work the whole time.

547
00:49:15,360 --> 00:49:16,680
She seemed stressed.

548
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:19,600
What exactly did you two fight about?

549
00:49:24,480 --> 00:49:26,920
Did you see her talking on the phone
with anyone else?

550
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:32,560
No, not really.

551
00:49:33,480 --> 00:49:35,280
There was no signal there.

552
00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:37,120
Why?

553
00:49:37,840 --> 00:49:39,720
Who do you think she was talking to?

554
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:44,440
I think she has someone else.

555
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:53,480
No way.

556
00:49:55,640 --> 00:49:56,760
How do you know?

557
00:49:59,720 --> 00:50:01,080
Just a guess.

558
00:50:01,160 --> 00:50:03,400
You two are always together.

559
00:50:03,480 --> 00:50:05,040
You even work at the same place.

560
00:50:05,120 --> 00:50:07,080
She hardly has any social circle,

561
00:50:07,160 --> 00:50:09,360
just Krarok, and Krarok is your sister.

562
00:50:09,960 --> 00:50:11,760
When would she have time for someone else?

563
00:50:15,440 --> 00:50:17,040
People can keep secrets,

564
00:50:18,360 --> 00:50:20,800
even when you're always together.

565
00:50:22,520 --> 00:50:24,320
If someone wants to hide something,

566
00:50:26,080 --> 00:50:28,600
they'll find a way
to get away with it somehow.

567
00:50:33,960 --> 00:50:37,400
I think Pie is hiding something from me.

568
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:39,880
I just don't know what it is.

569
00:50:47,760 --> 00:50:49,440
Why don't you talk to her?

570
00:50:52,800 --> 00:50:54,200
I'll talk to her for sure.

571
00:50:55,080 --> 00:50:56,760
But I won't ask her directly.

572
00:50:59,280 --> 00:51:00,520
I'll give her time.

573
00:51:02,720 --> 00:51:05,040
I'll give her a chance to tell me herself.

574
00:51:07,440 --> 00:51:09,640
But if she still won't tell me
what's in her heart,

575
00:51:10,160 --> 00:51:12,160
what she's hiding from me,

576
00:51:15,760 --> 00:51:17,880
I'll find out the truth myself.

577
00:51:49,200 --> 00:51:51,000
Pie, I'm coming in.

578
00:51:54,560 --> 00:51:56,520
Hey, Pie.

579
00:51:56,600 --> 00:51:59,440
Why take it down so soon? Pun even hired--

580
00:52:07,040 --> 00:52:08,080
Alright.

581
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:10,080
Pun's using money to fix everything again.

582
00:52:10,160 --> 00:52:11,960
It's not like that, Pie.

583
00:52:12,040 --> 00:52:14,640
He really put a lot of effort into it.

584
00:52:14,720 --> 00:52:16,800
- But he ran out of time because…
- I know, Mom.

585
00:52:18,120 --> 00:52:20,400
I understand Pun completely.

586
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:22,000
Forget it. It clutters the room.

587
00:52:22,080 --> 00:52:23,840
I was going to take it down anyway.

588
00:52:30,120 --> 00:52:33,400
Have you called Pun yet?

589
00:52:37,160 --> 00:52:38,520
You haven't, have you?

590
00:52:42,320 --> 00:52:45,200
Pie, get up and talk to me.

591
00:52:45,280 --> 00:52:47,800
What exactly did Pun do
to upset you this much?

592
00:52:47,880 --> 00:52:50,800
He's trying this hard,
and you still won't make up with him?

593
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:52,560
I'm not upset.

594
00:52:55,000 --> 00:52:58,320
It's just that if I go back, I'll run
into the same old problems again.

595
00:52:58,400 --> 00:53:00,680
The root of the problem
has never been resolved.

596
00:53:00,760 --> 00:53:02,480
Then what is the root of it, Pie?

597
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:05,480
- We can help fix it together.
- I have to tell him the truth, Mom.

598
00:53:07,080 --> 00:53:08,480
I have to let Pun know

599
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:11,080
I'm not the good person he thinks I am.

600
00:53:11,160 --> 00:53:13,680
I'm not some perfect woman
who's never made mistakes.

601
00:53:13,760 --> 00:53:16,920
I'm just a reckless girl
who once got pregnant.

602
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:18,000
I--

603
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:24,600
Pie.

604
00:53:25,760 --> 00:53:26,880
Pie, my dear.

605
00:53:27,960 --> 00:53:31,080
Pie. My dear.

606
00:53:32,280 --> 00:53:33,240
Pie.

607
00:53:33,760 --> 00:53:35,200
I'm sorry.

608
00:53:35,280 --> 00:53:38,080
Pie, I didn't mean to. I'm sorry.

609
00:53:39,840 --> 00:53:40,760
I…

610
00:53:41,280 --> 00:53:44,240
I really didn't mean to. It's just…

611
00:53:44,960 --> 00:53:49,280
I just don't want you
to talk about yourself like that.

612
00:53:49,360 --> 00:53:53,360
My daughter is a good person,
and you have everything going for you.

613
00:53:55,040 --> 00:53:57,280
Just one mistake

614
00:53:57,360 --> 00:54:01,880
doesn't make you any less worthy
of having a good husband.

615
00:54:07,360 --> 00:54:08,440
Pie.

616
00:54:09,840 --> 00:54:12,160
Don't dwell on the past.

617
00:54:12,920 --> 00:54:16,760
What's done is done.

618
00:54:18,280 --> 00:54:19,280
Right now,

619
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:24,240
you have a good life and a good family.

620
00:54:25,840 --> 00:54:28,480
Just forget it, okay?

621
00:54:30,880 --> 00:54:33,680
Don't let it ruin your life again, Pie.

622
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:40,040
I'm sorry, my dear. I'm sorry.

623
00:54:40,640 --> 00:54:42,440
Please forgive me, Pie.

624
00:54:43,160 --> 00:54:45,320
I didn't mean to.

625
00:54:45,840 --> 00:54:47,480
I'm sorry.

626
00:54:48,120 --> 00:54:50,720
But you have to trust me, okay?

627
00:54:50,800 --> 00:54:52,800
Please, Pie.

628
00:55:03,120 --> 00:55:05,160
I'm heading to the office now, Pun.
Are you okay?

629
00:55:05,240 --> 00:55:06,800
Should I take the day off?

630
00:55:06,880 --> 00:55:08,680
No need. Just go.

631
00:55:09,760 --> 00:55:11,320
My mind just won't stop racing.

632
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:13,120
I need to vent.

633
00:55:22,120 --> 00:55:24,000
You might be able to help me with this.

634
00:55:24,880 --> 00:55:26,400
Do you know this place?

635
00:55:40,280 --> 00:55:44,400
I asked Mom, I asked Rok,
everyone says Pie never had a boyfriend.

636
00:55:44,480 --> 00:55:47,480
That makes me want to know
who the guy in this photo is even more.

637
00:55:51,920 --> 00:55:53,040
You don't know?

638
00:55:54,560 --> 00:55:56,600
How would I know? The picture's not clear.

639
00:55:58,160 --> 00:56:00,200
I found it in Pie's bedroom.

640
00:56:00,880 --> 00:56:02,320
She kept it inside a book.

641
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:04,840
The photo's old, but she kept it.

642
00:56:05,440 --> 00:56:06,800
So it must be important.

643
00:56:07,880 --> 00:56:08,960
What do you think?

644
00:56:11,800 --> 00:56:13,320
No comment, Pun.

645
00:56:16,600 --> 00:56:19,000
That's a sensitive question.

646
00:56:19,600 --> 00:56:22,840
Let's just say I'll listen,
but I won't give my opinion.

647
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:28,040
Then just give me information.

648
00:56:29,800 --> 00:56:31,800
Do you know where this photo was taken?

649
00:56:33,320 --> 00:56:36,040
Well, it's hard to tell.

650
00:56:36,120 --> 00:56:38,160
Plenty of places have rides like this.

651
00:56:39,160 --> 00:56:40,400
Have you ever been on one?

652
00:56:40,920 --> 00:56:42,560
I guess I have.

653
00:56:44,280 --> 00:56:45,480
Who did you go with?

654
00:56:49,600 --> 00:56:51,000
By myself.

655
00:56:53,080 --> 00:56:54,680
Man, that's kind of lonely.

656
00:56:54,760 --> 00:56:56,760
Were you that bored, going by yourself?

657
00:57:02,040 --> 00:57:04,240
I've never seen this side of Pie before.

658
00:57:06,520 --> 00:57:08,840
I can't even picture her
doing anything this adventurous.

659
00:57:11,760 --> 00:57:13,040
Maybe…

660
00:57:14,280 --> 00:57:16,520
I never really knew her at all.

661
00:57:31,680 --> 00:57:35,160
I said things I didn't mean
because you asked me to.

662
00:57:35,720 --> 00:57:37,320
Want to know what it was about?

663
00:57:37,400 --> 00:57:38,360
Shut your mouth!

664
00:57:38,440 --> 00:57:39,440
Say it.

665
00:57:40,040 --> 00:57:41,360
I'm not a good person.

666
00:57:41,440 --> 00:57:42,880
You're just acting innocent.

667
00:57:42,960 --> 00:57:44,400
I'm not acting innocent.

668
00:57:44,480 --> 00:57:46,320
And I'm not pretending to be proper.

669
00:57:46,400 --> 00:57:48,520
This is just how I look, Mother.

670
00:57:48,600 --> 00:57:51,120
Pun still doesn't know
that I'm the man in the photo.

671
00:57:51,200 --> 00:57:53,520
He asked me about it,
but I didn't tell him.

672
00:57:53,600 --> 00:57:56,960
I used to date someone. That man was…

673
00:57:57,040 --> 00:57:58,040
Win.

674
00:58:00,800 --> 00:58:03,240
<i>What's in the past</i>
<i>should stay in the past.</i>

675
00:58:03,320 --> 00:58:08,720
We just need to face whatever comes next.

676
00:58:08,800 --> 00:58:10,440
Let's start over.

677
00:58:10,520 --> 00:58:12,920
I love you, Pie.

678
00:58:38,720 --> 00:58:41,600
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
